@node "Caratteristiche" "Specifications"
@{i}Introduction@{ui}

Thankyou  for  installing  the  "Atapi  Plug'n  Play"  kit.  Now  You  are the
owner of an hardware/software system with which You will be able use all the
last generation's CD-ROM ATAPI SFF-8020 drives connected to your Amiga.

We  inform  you  that  even  more  companies  are  releasing new ATAPI
products such as streamers, faster CD-ROM drives and CD-ROM drives for the
Write-Once CDs (CD-WO). The authors wants to support these new devices with
new releases of their product and they ask you kindly to contact them for
further informations.

(Programmers can refer to the @{"appendix B" link "Appendix_B" 0}).

Specifications

   *   @{"CD-ROM" link "CD-DRIVES" 0} IDE-ATAPI SFF 8020 compatibility
   *   Support for 4 Drives
   *   Software @{"driver" link "Appendix A" 0}
   *   @{"Filesystem" link "Filesystem" 0} ISO-9660, Rockridge and HFS compatible
   *   CD-AUDIO @{"player" link "MAP" 0}
   *   CDXL files @{"player" link "CDXL" 0} (Audio/Video)
   *   Tracks downloader software (@{"TrkDownLoad" link "TRKDL" 0})
   *   @{"Preferences" link "Preferenze" 0} program to make the device suitable for any CD-ROM drive
   *   CDł˛ high compatibility
   *   SCSI_Direct() protocol support
   *   SCSI-II emulation
   *   AmigaGuide documentation
   *   Programmers support @{"archive" link "Appendix_B" 0}
@endnode

